OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FFor most, a dry day with some
OL,6,Fbright or sunny spells. Turning
OL,7,Fcloudier in the afternoon as a band of
OL,8,Frain spreads eastwards into Argyll,
OL,9,Faccompanied by strengthening winds.
OL,10,FStaying dry elsewhere.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FA cloudy evening with rain
OL,13,Fand strong winds over Argyll at first
OL,14,Fspreading eastwards to all parts.
OL,15,FCloudy with outbreaks of rain
OL,16,Fovernight, becoming drier with clear
OL,17,Fspells towards dawn.
OL,18,
OL,19,CFriday:FA mixed day with some bright
OL,20,Fand sunny spells but also blustery
OL,21,Fshowers feeding in from the west.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
